Anica Third-Party Runtime Notice

This repository is licensed under Apache-2.0 unless a file states otherwise.

FFmpeg/FFprobe are separate upstream projects and are not relicensed by Apache-2.0.
By default, Anica expects users or development scripts to provide FFmpeg/FFprobe at runtime.

1) FFmpeg/FFprobe runtime
- Anica uses FFmpeg/FFprobe for preview decode, export, proxies, thumbnails, waveform preparation, and media analysis.
- If you redistribute FFmpeg binaries, include the applicable upstream license notices and source-obtain information for the exact build shipped.
- Prefer LGPL-only builds for redistributable app bundles.

Practical release rule
- Source-only distribution: state that FFmpeg/FFprobe are user-provided runtime tools.
- Bundled runtime distribution: include runtime license notices and source-obtain instructions.

